{"TopicId":82395,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Keep These Display Settings?","CreatedByName":"Sasuga","CreatedById":119064,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-22T00:30:33Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sasuga","CreatedById":119064,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-22T00:30:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E10...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E9...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E8...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E7...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E6...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E5...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E4...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E3...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E2...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E1...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI accidentally set my display settings way too big, and I couldn\u0027t reach the apply button to change them back.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dryer_lint","CreatedById":162541,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-22T01:56:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EGo fullscreen with Alt\u002BEnter, and then click on Apply.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vexx32","CreatedById":12283,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-22T03:45:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOr you can close KSP and directly edit the settings.cfg file.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut yes, something of this form would be a good idea.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}